    {
      "line": 992,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "their mothers, grandmothers, great-grandmothers .. . ‘Tus SET of interviews, then, documents the birth of heroes as it also documents the | birth of their children. It is part"
    },
    {
      "line": 1019,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "a kind of paleolithic Venus of Wil- lendorf icon? I interviewed European-Amer- ican, African-American and Asian- American women. I interviewed advocates of natural childbirth"
    },
    {
      "line": 1021,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "I interviewed European-Amer- ican, African-American and Asian- American women. I interviewed advocates of natural childbirth and women who used crack cocaine until the onset (early!) of their labor."
    },
    {
      "line": 1026,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "and women who used crack cocaine until the onset (early!) of their labor. I interviewed women who had brought babies to term and women who had miscarried and women who had delivered babies many"
    },
    {
      "line": 1030,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "who had miscarried and women who had delivered babies many weeks prematurely. I interviewed women who had had abortions. I interviewed married women and single mothers, heterosexuals and"
    },
    {
      "line": 1033,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "weeks prematurely. I interviewed women who had had abortions. I interviewed married women and single mothers, heterosexuals and lesbians, Catholics, Protestants, Muslims and Jews. Eventually the"
    },
    {
      "line": 1039,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "questions I asked assumed a uni- form format and became a stand- ardized interview, recorded as I spoke with each woman and transcribed afterward. Very little has been written about"
    },
    {
      "line": 1057,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "world at large. To use sexuality as an example: many of the women I interviewed reported that their sexual respon- siveness changed when they were pregnant. The quality of their or-"
    },
    {
      "line": 1107,
      "term": "interview",
      "snippet": "I also learned that, to a social an- thropologist from Mars who was * reading these interviews, there would be few clues that these women were reacting to the same experience. The process of birth is"
    },
    {
      "line": 2253,
      "term": "energy",
      "snippet": "yogic experiences. But then as other people began to home in on me, I lost access to that energy and I be- gan to feel ill and uncomfortable and nauseous and quite miserable. I woke up at three. At about nine"
    },
    {
      "line": 2386,
      "term": "community",
      "snippet": "asked them to recommend some- body and, of course, being in the medical community, they wouldn’t take sides so they gave me a list of about twelve names. I just had to take the luck of the draw."
    },
    {
      "line": 5788,
      "term": "software",
      "snippet": "the earth’s people. 27 GATES ROAD _ -- SAUSALITO, CA 94965 3 3 N THE FACE OF IT, “software for women” seems as bizarre and repulsive a concept as, say, cigarettes for women. It smacks of condescension, hand-holding, pastel"
    }
  ],
  "opening_lines": [
    {
      "line": 1,
      "text": "BIR THTALES"
    },
    {
      "line": 4,
      "text": "» at"
    },
    {
      "line": 12,
      "text": "“That's not the remarkable part,”"
    },
    {
      "line": 13,
      "text": "said my friend. “The remarkable part is how"
    },
    {
      "line": 14,
      "text": "much time she spends not doing any of that"
    },
    {
      "line": 15,
      "text": "- time spent waiting for and riding on buses,"
    },
    {
      "line": 16,
      "text": "time spent standing in line at various agen-"
    },
    {
      "line": 17,
      "text": "cies on behalf of her mother or her child,"
    },
    {
      "line": 18,
      "text": "time spent looking for bargains on baby"
    },
    {
      "line": 19,
      "text": "clothes and Pampers - just wasted time."
    },
    {
      "line": 20,
      "text": "People don’t realize how much hard work"
    },
    {
      "line": 21,
      "text": "is involved in just preventing yourself"
    },
    {
      "line": 22,
      "text": "from slipping beneath the underclass.”"
    },
    {
      "line": 25,
      "text": "And J hadn’t realized; I was too busy on"
    },
    {
      "line": 26,
      "text": "another level of abstraction. I"
    },
    {
      "line": 27,
      "text": "had realized all sorts of stuff"
    },
    {
      "line": 28,
      "text": "about poverty, had all sorts of"
    },
    {
      "line": 29,
      "text": "opinions, had changed my mind"
    },
    {
      "line": 30,
      "text": "several times about causes and"
    },
    {
      "line": 31,
      "text": "cures, and it had not actually oc-"
    },
    {
      "line": 32,
      "text": "curred to me how hard it would"
    },
    {
      "line": 33,
      "text": "be to raise yourself out of that"
    },
    {
      "line": 34,
      "text": "cycle if you were always riding"
    },
    {
      "line": 35,
      "text": "buses and filling out forms."
    },
    {
      "line": 38,
      "text": "What we lack about each other"
    },
    {
      "line": 39,
      "text": "is information. We have lots"
    },
    {
      "line": 41,
      "text": "of theories and lots of rhetoric and lots"
    },
    {
      "line": 43,
      "text": "of paradigms; we have lots of surveys and"
    },
    {
      "line": 44,
      "text": "pie charts and large-sample studies. But"
    },
    {
      "line": 46,
      "text": "we don’t have people saying to each other,"
    },
    {
      "line": 47,
      "text": "“This is how it is for me. This is what my life"
    },
    {
      "line": 48,
      "text": "is like; this is what I am. I am not a trend; I"
    },
    {
      "line": 49,
      "text": "am a contradiction. Now tell me about you.”"
    },
    {
      "line": 52,
      "text": "I think this is particularly true for men and"
    },
    {
      "line": 53,
      "text": "women in America right now. We censor"
    },
    {
      "line": 54,
      "text": "ourselves. We are uncomfortable"
    },
    {
      "line": 55,
      "text": "with ambivalence, in ourselves and"
    },
    {
      "line": 56,
      "text": "in others; we are uncomfortable"
    },
    {
      "line": 57,
      "text": "with the multitudes we all contain."
    },
    {
      "line": 58,
      "text": "We confine ourselves to pieties or"
    }
